  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddPartsController
    This class controls the AddParts.fxml scene and allows user to add a part to the Parts Table.
    AddProductsController
    This class controls the AddProducts.fxml scene and allows user to add a product to the Products Table.
    InHouse
    This class instantiates Inhouse Parts RUNTIME ERROR An error I encountered was trying to set the Inhouse Part attributes directly in this class instead of in the super class.
    Inventory
    This class controls the inventory of parts and products RUNTIME ERROR An error I encountered was trying to update parts/products by simply deleting and adding the part.
    Main
    This class instantiates the program by adding test data and launching the main screen RUNTIME ERROR An error I encountered in the code was that I had setup the sample data, however it was not launching when the program started.
    MainScreenController
    This class controls the main_screen.fxml scene and allows user to navigate to the needed parts/products scenes,as well as give the ability to see both tables.
    ModifyPartsController
    This class controls the ModifyParts.fxml scene and allows user to navigate to the modify parts scene which imports the selected product into the configurable fields.
    ModifyProductsController
    This class controls the ModifyProducts.fxml scene and allows user to add a product to the Products Table.
    OutsourcedPart
    This class controls the creation of Outsorced Parts RUNTIME ERROR An error I encountered was trying to reuse machineID for this class.
    Part  
    Product
